message: "If you use qctddft in published work, please cite the repository and version used."
title: "qctddft"
version: "1.2.0"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Liyanage"
    given-names: "Senal"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/fr-0zt/qctddft"
url: "https://github.com/fr-0zt/qctddft"
abstract: >-
  qctddft is a command-line toolkit for post-processing Q-Chem TDDFT calculations,
  including extraction of excitation data, spectrum generation, spectral-region
  identification, state assignment, and clustering of representative structures.
keywords:
  - computational chemistry
  - TDDFT
  - Q-Chem
  - excited states
  - spectroscopy
  - molecular modeling
